''Igor Omura Fraga''' (born September 26, 1998) is a [[Brazil]]ian born in Japan racing driver and [[Esports|eSports]] player. He is the incumbent champion of the [[2020 Toyota Racing Series|Toyota Racing Series]]  2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gtplanet.net/igor-fraga-wins-2020-toyota-racing-series/|title=Igor Fraga Wins 2020 Toyota Racing Series Title in Final Race Decider|date=2020-02-16|website=GTPlanet|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref> \n\nHe won the inaugural [[FIA Gran Turismo Championship|FIA Gran Turismo Nations Cup]] and McLaren Shadow racing series in 2018, and also competed in the [[2017 Formula One eSports Series]].<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.gran-turismo.com/gb/gtsport/livereport/00_8754344.html|title=The First Nations Cup Champion is Crowned! - gran-turismo.com|website=www.gran-turismo.com|language=en|access-date=2019-03-28}}</ref> 2020 he will compete in the [[FIA Formula 3 Championship|FIA-F3-Championship]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.f1-esports-finalist-igor-fraga-becomes-first-sim-racer-to-join-f3-grid.1JkYsrRdjBsxonwZdZuqwc.html|title=F1 Esports finalist Igor Fraga becomes first sim racer to join FIA F3 grid {{!}} Formula 1\u00ae|website=www.formula1.com|language=en|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>\n\n== Racing career ==\nFraga raced in [[Formula 3 Brasil]] for three years, all with Prop Car Racing. Fraga's first season in [[2015 Formula 3 Brasil season|2015]] did not start well, retiring in its first three races under Class B. The following race, he finished eighth overall, and third in his class. Fraga would earn a total of two pole positions, four fastest laps, nine podiums, and four class wins in the season and would finish third in Class B with 117 points.\n\nIn [[2016 Formula 3 Brasil season|2016]], Fraga was promoted to Class A, but only raced in four races, those being the first event at the Velopark and the last event at Interlagos. He would finish eleventh in the Class A standings, with one podium and 19 points. Fraga would return to the newly-renamed Academy class in 2017. Fraga won the class, finishing the season with 190 points, with seven pole positions, seven fastest laps, 13 podiums, and 10 class wins.\n\nSimultaneously with Formula 3 Brasil, Fraga also raced in [[NACAM Formula 4 Championship]] in 2017. In his only season in [[2017\u201318 NACAM Formula 4 Championship|2017\u201318]], Fraga finished second overall and earned 286 points, with five pole positions, seven fastest laps, 12 podiums, and six race wins.\n\nIn 2018, Fraga participated in the [[U.S. F2000 National Championship]]. He ended the season in fourth overall, with three podiums and 213 points.\n\n2019 Fraga made his European debut in the inaugural [[Formula Regional European Championship]], winning four races and finishing 3rd and therefore best of the non-[[Prema Powerteam|Prema]] drivers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://the-race.com/esports/can-an-esports-star-end-brazils-f1-drought/|title=Can an Esports star end Brazil's F1 drought?|date=2020-02-23|website=The Race|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref> \n\nIn 2020, Fraga will participate in the [[FIA Formula 3 Championship]], driving alongside [[David Schumacher (racing driver)|David Schumacher]], son of F1 Grand Prix winner [[Ralf Schumacher]], and series veteran, [[Niko Kari]]. All three of these drivers will be racing for the Czech Republic based [[Charouz Racing System]].<ref name=\":3\" /> In March of that year, Fraga was named as a new signing to the [[Red Bull Junior Team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://juniorteam.redbull.com/article/igor-fraga-joins-red-bull-junior-team|title=Igor Fraga joins the Red Bull Junior Team|date=March 16, 2020|accessdate=March 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nFraga was born in [[Kanazawa]], [[Japan]] to [[Brazil|Brazilian]] parents.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mclaren.com/racing/2018/mclaren-shadow-project/getting-to-know-igor-5123217/|title=McLaren Racing - Getting to know: Igor Fraga|website=www.mclaren.com|language=en|access-date=2019-06-22}}</ref> He is a [[Multilingualism|multilinguist]], capable of speaking [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]], English, [[Japanese language|Japanese]], and [[Spanish language|Spanish]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usf2000.com/teams-drivers/current-drivers/igor-fraga|title=Igor Fraga - USF2000.com|website=USF2000|access-date=2019-06-22}}</ref>\n\n==Racing record==\n===Career summary===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 90%; text-align:center\"\n! Season\n! Series\n! Team\n! Races\n! Wins\n! Poles\n! F/Laps\n! Podiums\n! Points\n! Position\n|-\n! 2015\n|align=left| [[2015 Formula 3 Brasil season|F\u00f3rmula 3 Brasil - Class B]]\n|rowspan=4 align=left| Prop Car Racing\n| 16\n| 4\n| 2\n| 4\n| 9\n| 117\n|style=\"background:#FFDF9F;\" | '''3rd'''\n|-\n! 2016\n|align=left| [[2016 Formula 3 Brasil season|F\u00f3rmula 3 Brasil]]\n| 4\n| 0\n| 0\n| 0\n| 1\n| 19\n| 11th\n|-\n! 2017\n|align=left| [[2017 Formula 3 Brasil season|F\u00f3rmula 3 Brasil - Academy Class]]\n| 16\n| 10\n| 7\n| 7\n| 13\n| 190\n|style=\"background:#FFFFBF;\"| '''1st'''\n|-\n! 2017-18\n|align=left| [[2017-18 NACAM Formula 4 Championship|NACAM Formula 4 Championship]]\n| 18\n| 6\n| 5\n| 7\n| 12\n| 280\n|style=\"background:#DFDFDF;\"| '''2nd'''\n|-\n! 2018\n|align=left| [[2018 U.S. F2000 National Championship|U.S. F2000 National Championship]]\n|align=left| Exclusive Autosport\n| 14\n| 0\n| 0\n| 0\n| 3\n| 213\n| 4th\n|-\n! 2019\n|align=left| [[2019 Formula Regional European Championship|Formula Regional European Championship]]\n|align=left| [[RP Motorsport|DR Formula by RP Motorsport]]\n| 24\n| 4\n| 4\n| 3\n| 11\n| 300\n|style=\"background:#FFDF9F;\"| '''3rd'''\n|-\n!2020\n|align=left| [[2020 Toyota Racing Series|Toyota Racing Series]]\n|align=left| [[M2 Competition (team)|M2 Competition]]\n|15\n|4\n|3\n|3\n|9\n|362\n|style=\"background:#FFFFBF;\"| '''1st'''\n|-\n|}\n\n===Complete U.S. F2000 National Championship res