w.soundtrackinfo.com/title/powerofone.asp|work=soundtrackinfo.com|publisher=The Soundtrack Info Project|accessdate=15 March 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title= Remembering Johnny Clegg's Powerful Mission / South Africa's best-known musician has dedicated his life to crossing the lines separating white and black|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/johnny-clegg-apartheid-south-africa-860407/|work=rollingstone.com|publisher=RollingStone|accessdate=21 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official}}\n* [http://inmyafricandream.free.fr/ In My African Dream: the Johnny Clegg Discography] inmyafricandream.free.fr\n* Greg Kot: [https://web.archive.org/web/20050913023809/http://www.talkingleaves.com/articles/worlds.html Worlds Apart: Johnny Clegg Has Been / Molded by South Africa] [[Chicago Tribune]] April 29, 1990\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070927191703/http://www.talkingleaves.com/pithouse.html A National Treasure Turns 21] talkingleaves.com October 25, 2000\n* Jeremy Cooper: [https://web.archive.org/web/20070223235202/http://www.chico.mweb.co.za/art/2006/2006dec/061215-zulu.html The return of the white Zulu] chico.mweb.co 15 December 2006\n* {{discogs artist}}\n* {{Find a Grave|201345469}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Clegg, Johnny}}\n[[Category:1953 births]]\n[[Category:2019 deaths]]\n[[Category:Jewish South African anti-apartheid activists]]\n[[Category:White South African anti-apartheid activists]]\n[[Category:British emigrants to Rhodesia]]\n[[Category:Rhodesian emigrants to South Africa]]\n[[Category:Capitol Records artists]]\n[[Category:Concertina players]]\n[[Category:Jewish English musicians]]\n[[Category:People from Bacup]]\n[[Category:Officers of the Order of the British Empire]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Order of Ikhamanga]]\n[[Category:South African anthropologists]]\n[[Category:South African musicians]]\n[[Category:Secular Jews]]\n[[Category:English emigrants to South Africa]]\n[[Category:South African people of English-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:South African people of Lithuanian-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:South African people of Polish-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:South African people of Scottish descent]]\n[[Category:South African people of Zimbabwean descent]]\n[[Category:South African pop singers]]\n[[Category:University of the Witwatersrand alumni]]\n[[Category:Juluka members]]\n[[Category:Savuka members]]\n[[Category:Deaths from cancer in South Africa]]\n[[Category:Deaths from pancreatic cancer]]\n[[Category:English people of Polish-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:English people of Lithuanian-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:English people of Scottish descent]]\n[[Category:English people of Zimbabwean descent]]\n[[Category:Burials at Westpark Cemetery]]\n", "name_user": "Edwin of Northumbria", "label": "safe", "comment": "Expanded ref.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Johnny_Clegg"}
{"title_page": "HOTTIP", "text_new": "In [[molecular biology]], '''HOTTIP''' ('''HO'''XA '''t'''ranscript at the distal '''tip''') is a [[long non-coding RNA]]. The gene encoding HOTTIP is located at the [[5\u2032]] tip of the [[Hox gene|HOXA]] locus, and coordinates the [[Regulation of gene expression|activation]] of several of the 5\u2032 HOXA genes. The non-coding RNA is brought into close proximity with the HOXA genes by [[chromosomal]] looping. HOTTIP binds to the [[WDR5]] protein, which forms a complex with the [[histone methyltransferase]] protein [[MLL (gene)|MLL]]. This targets the WDR5-MLL complex to the HOXA region and results in H3K4 methylation and transcriptional activation of the HOXA locus.<ref name=\"pmid21423168\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Wang KC, Yang YW, Liu B, Sanyal A, Corces-Zimmerman R, Chen Y, etal | title=A long noncoding RNA maintains active chromatin to coordinate homeotic gene expression. | journal=Nature | year= 2011 | volume= 472 | issue= 7341 | pages= 120\u2013124 | pmid=21423168 | doi=10.1038/nature09819 | pmc= 3670758| url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/eutils/elink.fcgi?dbfrom=pubmed&tool=sumsearch.org/cite&retmode=ref&cmd=prlinks&id=21423168  }}</ref>\nMore recently, HOTTIP has been shown to play a role in Hepatocellular Carcinoma (HCC) progression. HOTTIP expression levels predict metastasis formation and poor disease outcome in HCC patients.\n<ref>{{cite journal | pmid = 24114970 | doi=10.1002/hep.26740 | volume=59 | issue=3 | title=Long noncoding RNA HOTTIP/HOXA13 expression is associated with disease progression and predicts outcome in hepatocellular carcinoma patients | pmc=3943759 | year=2014 | journal=Hepatology | pages=911\u201323  | last1 = Quagliata | first1 = L | last2 = Matter | first2 = MS | last3 = Piscuoglio | first3 = S | last4 = Arabi | first4 = L | last5 = Ruiz | first5 = C | last6 = Procino | first6 = A | last7 = Kovac | first7 = M | last8 = Moretti | first8 = F | last9 = Makowska | first9 = Z | last10 = Boldanova | first10 = T | last11 = Andersen | first11 = JB | last12 = H\u00e4mmerle | first12 = M | last13 = Tornillo | first13 = L | last14 = Heim | first14 = MH | last15 = Diederichs | first15 = S | last16 = Cillo | first16 = C | last17 = Terracciano | first17 = LM}}</ref> HOTTIP has been shown to be transcriptionally regulated by a transcriptional coactivator PSIP1/p52<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Pradeepa|first=Madapura M.|last2=McKenna|first2=Fionnuala|last3=Taylor|first3=Gillian C. A.|last4=Bengani|first4=Hemant|last5=Grimes|first5=Graeme R.|last6=Wood|first6=Andrew J.|last7=Bhatia|first7=Shipra|last8=Bickmore|first8=Wendy A.|date=2017-04-06|title=Psip1/p52 regulates posterior Hoxa genes through activation of lncRNA Hottip|url=http://journals.plos.org/plosgenetics/article?id=10.1371/journal.pgen.1006677|journal=PLOS Genetics|volume=13|issue=4|pages=e1006677|doi=10.1371/journal.pgen.1006677|issn=1553-7404|pmc=5383017|pmid=28384324}}</ref>\n* [[Long noncoding RNA]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*  {{cite journal| author=Burgess DJ| title=Non-coding RNA: HOTTIP goes the distance. | journal=Nat Rev Genet | year= 2011 | volume= 12 | issue= 5 | pages= 300 | pmid=21483457 | doi=10.1038/nrg2992 | pmc= | url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/eutils/elink.fcgi?dbfrom=pubmed&tool=sumsearch.org/cite&retmode=ref&cmd=prlinks&id=21483457  }}\n\n[[Category:Non-coding RNA]]\n", "text_old": "In [[molecular biology]], '''HOTTIP''' ('''HO'''XA '''t'''ranscript at the distal '''tip''') is a [[long non-coding RNA]]. The gene encoding HOTTIP is located at the [[5\u2032]] tip of the [[Hox gene|HOXA]] locus, and coordinates the [[Regulation of gene expression|activation]] of several of the 5\u2032 HOXA genes. The non-coding RNA is brought into close proximity with the HOXA genes by [[chromosomal]] looping. HOTTIP binds to the [[WDR5]] protein, which forms a complex with the [[histone methyltransferase]] protein [[MLL (gene)|MLL]]. This targets the WDR5-MLL complex to the HOXA region and results in H3K4 methylation and transcriptional activation of the HOXA locus.<ref name=\"pmid21423168\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Wang KC, Yang YW, Liu B, Sanyal A, Corces-Zimmerman R, Chen Y, etal | title=A long noncoding RNA maintains active chromatin to coordinate homeotic gene expression. | journal=Nature | year= 2011 | volume= 472 | issue= 7341 | pages= 120\u2013124 | pmid=21423168 | doi=10.1038/nature09819 | pmc= 3670758| url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/eutils/elink.fcgi?dbfrom=pubmed&tool=sumsearch.org/cite&retmode=ref&cmd=prlinks&id=21423168  }}</ref>\nMore recently, HOTTIP has been shown to play a role in Hepatocellular Carcinoma (HCC) progression. HOTTIP expression levels predict metastasis formation and poor disease outcome in HCC patients.\n<ref>Quagliata L, Matter MS, Piscuoglio S, Arabi L, Ruiz C, Procino A, Kovac M, Moretti F, Makowska Z, Boldanova T, Andersen JB, H\u00e4mmerle M, Tornillo L, Heim MH, Diederichs S, Cillo C, Terracciano LM. \"lncRNA HOTTIP / HOXA13 expression is associated with disease progression and predicts outcome in hepatocellular carcinoma patients. Hepatology. 2013 Sep 20. doi: 10.1002/hep.26740. {{PMID|24114970}}</ref> HOTTIP has been shown to be transcriptionally regulated by a transcriptional coactivator PSIP1/p52<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Pradeepa|first=Madapura M.|last2=McKenna|first2=Fionnuala|last3=Taylor|first3=Gillian C. A.|last4=Bengani|first4=Hemant|last5=Grimes|first5=Graeme R.|last6=Wood|first6=Andrew J.|last7=Bhatia|first7=Shipra|last8=Bickmore|first8=Wendy A.|date=2017-04-06|title=Psip1/p52 regulates posterior Hoxa genes through activation of lncRNA Hottip|url=http://journals.plos.org/plosgenetics/article?id=10.1371/journal.pgen.1006677|journal=PLOS Genetics|volume=13|issue=4|pages=e1006677|doi=10.1371/journal.pgen.1006677|issn=1553-7404|pmc=5383017|pmid=28384324}}</ref>\n* [[Long noncoding RNA]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*  {{cite journal| author=Burgess DJ| title=Non-coding RNA: HOTTIP goes the distance. | journal=Nat Rev Genet | year= 2011 | volume= 12 | issue= 5 | pages= 300 | pmid=21483457 | doi=10.1038/nrg2992 | pmc= | url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/eutils/elink.fcgi?dbfrom=pubmed&tool=sumsearch.org/cite&retmode=ref&cmd=prlinks&id=21483457  }}\n\n[[Category:Non-coding RNA]]\n", "name_user": "Rjwilmsi", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Journal cites:,", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HOTTIP"}
{"title_page": "Abbah", "text_new": "\n\n'''Sweetbert Charles''' (born in 14 February 1988 In [[Dar es Salaam]]), known by his stage name '''Abbah Process''' a.k.a. \"Beat monster\" is a Tanzanian Recording artist, Record producer. He is the CEO of Abbah Music Studios. Also he is a Co-Founder and member of the Abbah Music Recording Label. He has produced ulbums for and overseen the careers of many rappers and singers including [[Harmonize (musician)|Harmonize]], [[Sho Madjozi]], [[Nandy (singer)|Nandy]], Darassa, Marioo, Jux, Maua sama, [[Ycee]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://afrikalyrics.com/artist/abbah|title=Abbah - Biography, Lyrics and Videos {{!}} AfrikaLyrics|website=Afrika Lyrics|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allafricamusic.com/show/abbah|title=#Abbah|website=AllAfricaMusic.Com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://genius.com/artists/Abbah-process|title=Abbah Process|website=Genius|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref> He is credited as the Key figure in the popularization of Young Tanzanian Music Producers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wikiwand.com/en/Music_of_Tanzania|title=Music of Tanzania - Wikiwand|website=www.wikiwand.com|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>\n\n== Early Life ==\nAbbah started to place his interests in [[Music]] when he was at the age of 11, they sat down with his brother their father once asked them both what they would like when he came home from work, Abbah chose a keyboard and her brother chose a school bag<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mwananchi.co.tz/habari/Makala/Abbah--Kichwa-nyuma-ya-nyimbo-za-Darassa/1597592-3817982-nyhkkd/index.html|title=Abbah: Kichwa nyuma ya nyimbo za Darassa|website=Mwananchi|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>. Officially he began his music career as an assistant music producer at Natal Records [[Mburahati]],[[Dar es Salaam]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bongo5.com/producer-abbah-wasanii-wanazingua-sana-ukiwaambia-njoo-tusaini-mikataba-wapiga-chenga-video-04-2020/|title=Producer Abbah: Wasanii wanazingua sana, ukiwaambia njoo tusaini mikataba wapiga chenga (Video)|date=2020-04-08|website=Bongo5.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref> He worked there for the period of 3 Years before leaving and started his own studio. His first Artist to sign under his management (Abbah Music Label) Marioo, Abbah introduced him to music industry and achieve great achievements and he was nominated for an award for best new African artist in south africa <ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.bbc.com/pidgin/tori-51081595|title=Marioo nominated at soundcity MVP award|date=2020-01-12|work=BBC News Pidgin|access-date=2020-04-17|url-status=live}}</ref>. And through his music studio he produced a Darassa song that called \"Muziki\" he was able to gain great popularity through the song,  was a great success and received a nomination for the award for African fans favorite artist.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://millardayo.com/gt5832/|title=Good News: Watanzania 10 wametajwa kuwania Tuzo za AFRIMA 2017 \u2013 Millardayo.com|last=TZA|first=Makoleko|website=millardayo.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://trace.tv/trace-mziki/music/news/video-week-darassa-muziki-ft-ben-pol/|title=MZIKI FRESHI : Darassa - Muziki (ft. Ben Pol)|date=2016-11-27|website=Trace Mziki|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>\n\n== Abbah Music ==\nAbbah opened his own company called Abbah Music, that compromised Abbah Music studios (Label, Training centre for new Producers, management, PR). Abbah music has since then work upon major many projects with different Artists and companies. Abbah Music Label manages many artists and music producers including Marioo, kapipo and Byta beast.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thedailybreakingnews.com/africa/eastern-africa/tanzania/producer-abbah-amtambulisha-msanii-mpya-bytar-afananishwa-na-burna-boy-video/|title=Producer Abbah amtambulisha msanii mpya Bytar, afananishwa na Burna Boy (Video)|last=Tanzania|first=Tdbn-|date=2020-04-07|website=World's Breaking News Journal {{!}} TDBN {{!}}|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://genius.com/artists/Kapipo-beatz|title=Kapipo beatz|website=Genius|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref> \n\nAbbah together with Mario, Kapipo from his music record Label they become popular with their single \"Chibonge\" and managed to be a hit In Africa<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.musicinafrica.net/magazine/top-10-bongo-flava-songs-2019|title=Top 10 bongo flava songs of 2019|date=2019-09-16|website=Music In Africa|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>\n\n'''<big>PORTFORIO</big>'''\n\n* Rich mavoko ft. Fid Q - Sherii (2017)\n* Darassa ft. Ben pol - Muziki (2017)\n* Abbah x Marioo x Bita beast (2019)\n*[[Rayvanny]] x [[Mayorkun]] - Gimmie Dat <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://justnaija.com/rayvanny-gimi-dat-ft-mayorkun-m786/|title=Rayvanny - Gimi Dat Ft. Mayorkun|last=Gift|date=2019-10-10|website=JustNaija|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>\n* Maua Sama x Hanstone - Iokote (2018)\n* Jux - Unaniweza (2020)\n* Luludiva x Richmavoko - Ona (2017)\n* Dayna Nyange\n* Fid Q ft. Isha Mashauzi x Rich mavoko x BIG jah man\n*Young D ft. Abbah - gali yangu\n*shose ft Abbah - Falling in Love\n\n== External Links ==\n\n* Website <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abbah-music.com/#contact-head-section|title=Eskino|website=abbah-music.com|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref><br />\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n[[Category:Tanzania articles by importance]]\n[[Category:Music production]]\n[[Category:Producers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Tanzanian artists]]\n[[Category:1988]]\n", "text_old": "\n\n'''Sweetbert Charles''' (born in 14 February 1988 In [[Dar es Salaam]]), known by his stage name '''Abbah Process''' Aka \"Beat monster\" is a Tanzanian Recording artist, Record producer. He is the CEO of Abbah Music Studios. Also he is a Co-Founder and member of